im dry now for like 21 days again
but im starting to get bored
my flat is clean, work is going well, i dont have arguments with people fully hammered
sometimes i just crave for the bottle to have action again
but then i look back at the horrors i have with withdrawel and the wake nights were i just lie in bed thinking my internals are gonna quit

long story short
i miss drinking, i love drinking
but i shouldnt be doing it anymore if i want to live on, so i burried the bottle
everyday without my trusty bottle is a fight
i just never loved someone as much as i loved bewhining myself for being lonely and flushing it down with liquor

every day feels the same

get up
make coffee
take a shower
go to work
clean flat
sleep
repeat

just replace working with playing video games on the weekend
it just feels like everything is so normal

and than you hear the bottle whisper
Oi ! Terminus, want some fun ?
Just unscrew me and fill in.

posts.com:
I think I'm starting to get it. I think alcohol started to feel bad because real life started to feel bad. I was being dragged back into the 3D world again for unrelated circumstances, and alcohol stopped being about fun and started to be about running away. When I woke up sick and hungover and brain chemistry out of wack because I drank too hard to get further away, the 3D world still yanked my leash and dragged me back. It filled me with dirty and ugly feelings that I hated myself for having. Frustration, spite, irritability, hate, anxiety, paranoia, and I started to lash out. This all made it worse, and made me feel worse about myself. It has created a spiral.
I will never forgive the 3D world for tainting my feelings and the things I love. And I love a good drink.
